==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matross
<hw>Ma*tross"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>matroos</ets>, fr. F. <ets>matelot</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>Formerly, in the British service, a gunner or a gunner's mate; one
of the soldiers in a train of artillery, who assisted the gunners in
loading, firing, and sponging the guns.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matt</ent>⟦br⟧
